This function now has a time complexity of O(log(min(m, n))) because at each recursive step, it discards a portion of one of the lists, and the size of the problem is reduced by approximately half. This is a significant improvement over the linear complexity approach, especially when k is much smaller than the sum of the lengths of the two lists.

